title: For Sale:  COBRAY LHC STREET SWEEPER LADIES HOME COMPANION 45-70 / 410
postcontent:
For Sale – This is a Cobray (SWD, Later known as Cobray and Leinad), Ladies Home Companion (LHC), AKA- The Mini Street Sweeper. It is made in the USA and a copy of the South African design.

* It is chambered in 410 shotshell , 45-70 government rounds, or .45 Long Colt.

* It is officially classified by the ATF as a pistol/revolver that’s why it has no stock or forward pistol grip. I guess in a way you could call it a revolver since the drum does not remove for reloading.

* It holds 12 rounds with a built in drum.

* These units are NOT listed as a destructive device. When the Street Sweeper became listed as a Destructive Device, Cobray used some of their tooling to create the LHC.

* The 45-70 pistols do have a grooved barrel and operates exactly like the 12 gauge units.

* This unit was completely refurbished. The main spring and trigger group were degreased and re- oiled to ensure a long service life. The unit looks and functions like new. Very few of these units exist and this is a wonderful addition to any firearm collection.

* Weighs about 12 pounds, has a 25 lbs trigger pull and can all be release in about 3 seconds.

* Very few of these are on the open market.

* These were made by Cobray, which also produced the Street Sweeper shotgun.

* If you”re wondering why Cobray chose that name (Ladies Home Companion), it’s because the Street Sweeper’s name was partially why it got targeted by politicians. Rather than choose something menacing, they went with something friendly.

title: For Sale:  1961 M101A1 3/4 Military Trailer
postcontent:
For sale is a 1961, M101A1 3/4 Military Trailer. $800 obo

Last assignment was a Missouri National Guard unit. Retains Pvt. Soup Sandwich's wonderful 3-tone NATO Woodland pattern depot paint job. 

Trailer is lucky enough to be covered most of it's life, as there is very little rust in the usual spot up front in the bed. The minimal rust that is there appears to be primarily from water backsplash from the tow vehicle. You can see the remains of the old MERCD camo pattern, and the OD before that. There's probably 20 pounds of CARC paint on this thing, so rest assured the metal underneath it is well protected as is.

All lights work (24v). Parking brakes work great (right one could use a tension adjustment). 

New tires with 1700 miles on them ($600), new slave cable for 24-volt hookup, new 3-tone Woodland synthetic top ($330). Doors/chains/wood are present and in nice shape. All bows are present (two of them updated to newer style aluminum). Also includes an extra set of tires that were new four years ago, but were replaced for a cross country trip as a precaution. "Kick-stands" present and working.

Note: Bows and Tarp not shown in photos

Trailer has been garaged for the past two years for potential restoration/repaint, and is currently buried as a moveable storage unit for boxes etc. in our garage. Will pull out for serious inquiries. Trailers in this condition typically sell for about $1300-$1600.

This would make a great trailer for the military vehicle collector, strong candidate for a bug-out or off-road camper, or ready to go to work as a wood/farm trailer. 

I'm selling my M1009 (seen in the photos), so you will need a vehicle with a pintle hitch to tow it home. Or, it's easy enough for one guy to roll around on level ground. Two guys and a winch could easily walk it up on a flatbed trailer.

If you're interested in the M1009 CUCV (Military K5 Blazer) seen in the photo, let me know and we could work out a package deal.

postcontent:
For sale is a Walther PPS in .40S&W, manufactured in 2011 and purchased in April 2012.

Link to extended album of full-resolution photos:
http://imgur.com/a/16R6j

Included with the pistol are the original hard case, the two factory magazines (6-round with half extension and 7-round with full extension), both the standard and large backstraps, one Blackhawk CQC Single-Stack magazine carrier, one Galco Stow N' Go IWB clip holster, one Crossbreed Supertuck IWB holster, the owner's manual and test-fired shell casing, and five Pachmayr snap caps.

The pistol was originally owned by my brother, who used it as a primary CCW for a little over a year and a half.  As such it has some minor indication of holster wear, but is in overall great condition with no damage to the slide finish and a nice shiny barrel.  It has seen an estimated 700-800 rounds of various FMJ loads as well as 165-grain Speer Gold Dot, and it has cycled everything without failure.

The magazine with the full extension has two minor rust spots, one by the feed lips and the other by the baseplate.  The Crossbreed holster has a small crack in the kydex shell that should be easily repaired with some plastic epoxy.  These can be seen in the full-resolution photo album I have linked.  The fit of the Crossbreed has loosened over time and can be tightened to your liking using a hair dryer, though when worn it still retains well.  All other accessories are in good condition.

Asking price for everything is $475, reasonable offers will be considered.  I am not interested in trades.

I am willing to ship to FFL, buyer pays shipping and transfer fees.

title: For Sale:  US Danish M1 Garand, .30-06
postcontent:
This is a US lend-lease rifle re-imported through the Civilian Marksmanship Program from Denmark.  After WW2, many US M1 Garands were rebarelled, test fired for action checking, and then shipped abroad to arm our allies in case of Communist attack.  Some rifles saw a lot of use.  Others, like the Danish Garands, sat in the warehouse the entire time, safely preserved and packed away, until the Lend-Lease program expired, and they were sent back.

The Danish Garands are considered some of the finest CMP rifles available.  It has an almost brand new barrel, and was hand chosen by a grizzled old CMP employee as one of the best on the show racks, showing the least amount of muzzle throat erosion at the Camp Perry Store.

Asking price is $850, cash.  No trades please.  Deal will be made in person, no shipping.  Contact me through Armslist if you have questions.
